This paper deals with the Travelling Salesman Problem (TSP), which is a classic problem in computer science and falls under the category of algorithms and data structures (cs.DS). The paper also involves combinatorial optimization techniques, which are often used in theoretical computer science and fall under the category of computational complexity (cs.CC). The problem of finding the integrality gap for the LP relaxation of TSP is a graph theory problem, which falls under the category of graph theory (cs.GT). The paper also involves optimization techniques, which fall under the category of operations research (cs.OC). Finally, the paper involves the use of machine learning techniques, which fall under the category of machine learning (cs.LG).
